\@writefile{toc}{\contentsline {paragraph}{(a) Cost-driven asymmetric step sizes.}{6}{}\protected@file@percent }
\@writefile{toc}{\contentsline {paragraph}{(b) Exponential backoff.}{6}{}\protected@file@percent }
\@writefile{toc}{\contentsline {paragraph}{(c) Continuous adjustment range.}{7}{}\protected@file@percent }
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {3}{\ignorespaces CRAFT core feedback loop. The per-bank timeout counter triggers a speculative precharge, whose outcome is classified into one of three categories. An incorrect speculative precharge incurs $t_\mathrm  {RP} + t_\mathrm  {RCD}$ in avoidable overhead and escalates the timeout with exponential backoff. A correct speculative precharge confirms the current timeout value. A conflict incurs only $t_\mathrm  {RP}$ in missed overlap opportunity and de-escalates the timeout by a cost-proportional decrement.}}{7}{}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:feedback}{{3}{7}{}{figure.3}{}}
